{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "However, this would introduce excessive costs (both in terms of money and performance), since each prompt would include a long sequence of textual examples.",
    "Hence, following the Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) principle [35], we include only the 𝑘 examples in E that are the most semantically similar to the input window.",
    "More formally, given a textual representation 𝑇 (𝑤 𝑡) of a window 𝑤 𝑡 currently processed by ADL-LLM, we compute the corresponding embedding 𝜙 𝑤 𝑡 = Φ(𝑇 (𝑤 𝑡)), where Φ is a function (e.g., a pre-trained LLM) mapping sentences into a latent space representation (i.e., their embedding).",
    "Then, for each pair (𝑇 (𝑤), 𝐴) ∈ E, we compute the pairwise cosine similarity between 𝜙 𝑤 𝑡 and 𝜙 𝑤 = Φ(𝑇 (𝑤)).",
    "We enrich the system prompt with the 𝑘 pairs (𝑇 (𝑤), 𝐴) ∈ 𝐸 that are associated with the highest pairwise similarity between 𝜙 𝑤 𝑡 and 𝜙 𝑤."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Hence, following the Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) principle [35], we include only the 𝑘 examples in E that are the most semantically similar to the input window."
  ]
}